commit.message: Switch build status button to travis-ci.com

Update Travis build environment

This also switches to a newer method for specifying extra packages to
install.

Use apt for Debian and Ubuntu package installation

It was mentioned in #67 that aptitude isn't present by default in
Debian, and apt seems to be the preferred tool now.
Apply naming standards across the codebase

Inline cmp_by_atime in StatsCache

This is simple enough it should just be a lambda.
Address warnings from newest clang-tidy
Clean up unused logic in fpcompare

Convert mp3fs.h to C++

This uses standard C++ syntax for the params struct.
Reformat markdown according to latest pandoc

Add tip regarding mount dependencies

Requested in #65.
Release version 1.1.1

Fix source path determination for transcoding

Using a glob for this logic does not work well, because certain common
characters like square brackets get interpreted specially. Instead, we
need to just implement the prefix checking ourselves.

This also updates the tests to catch this particular problem.

Fixes #66.
Release version 1.1
Remove unused VERSION variable in Dockerfile
Add missing flag output for log_format

Add support for custom log entry formats

This also includes the thread ID in log lines by default, so
multithreaded file operations can be debugged effectively.

Rationalize mp3fs treatment of file sizes

When an encode is finished, the number of bytes returned by the encoder
might differ from the number calculated at the beginning. This change
ensures that the number of bytes returned always matches the result of a
stat operation. If the stat cache is enabled, we can return the number
of bytes according to the encoder; since the size is cached, this will
match a future stat. If it is disabled, we must make the file size match
what we computed, either by truncating or extending.

In either case, the ID3v1 tag must remain intact in the correct position
in order to remain valid, which this change also ensures.

This also removes the "actual size" logic from the encoder and the
stored size from the transcoder, both of which are no longer needed.
Instead, the buffer size is used as the file size.

Fix logic for retrieving valid data

When transcoding is finished, buffer_.tell() points to the last position
the encoder wrote to, but does not include the ID3v1 tag. The existing
logic failed to read that data, leading to additional reads being
necessary, and possibly confusing some programs.

Redesign Buffer to track end bytes separately

This requires callers to explicitly specify whether they want data to go
in the main portion or the end, but results in a significantly simpler
implementation.

Increase severity for top-level file op logging

This also adds an extra debug log statement during transcoding.
Fix log severity for LAME messages
Add rule to run fast (subsecond) static checks

Remove error when encoder or decoder are closed

This isn't needed; they are only closed when transcoding is finished,
and at that point it's fine to simply provide what's in the buffer.

Inline transcode_until into read method

It's called nowhere else, and keeping it separate doesn't serve any
useful purpose.

Remove actual_size from Mp3Encoder constructor

The only place it's used is in render_tag, so just pass the file size
into that method instead.

This also corrects the logged sizes in Transcoder::finish to actually
use the calculated size.

Build Docker image based on local files

This makes it possible to build an image at any revision or even based
on local modifications.

Fix link to image on Docker Hub

This also slighly clarifies the wording (there was an unclear pronoun).

Use variable for version number in Dockerfile

This makes it easier to update when a new version is released.

Add helper function for checking equality in tests

This outputs the values being tested, to make problems easier to
diagnose.

Add test for readlink behavior

This was missing previously.
